thread.title: SAC starts fall/winter season

title: SAC starts fall/winter season
text:
SAC starts fall/winter season 0 comments 
Twenty-four Shippensburg Aquatic Club swimmers competed this past weekend at the West Shore YMCA A/BB/C Meet at Cumberland Valley, were they got their fall/winter season off to a terrific start with the swimmers posting 62 new personal best times. 
Six SAC club records were also broken: Brandon Estep in the 100 fly, Jillian Strine in the 200 free, Lek Powell in the 50 back, Makenna Morris in the 200 back, Sam Nonemaker in the 200 back, and Caleb Eveland in the 200 fly. kAmp=D@[ ?6H $9:A DH:>>6C w@==J v665J 4@>A6E65 :?
